be proud of what youve achieved, no matter how big or small it may be, bc it was a difficult ass battle you just fought and you WON 

no one can take that away from you
even if the problem doesnt seem huge and world-altering in the grand scheme of things or in the eyes of others, your battles are your own and their significance can only be defined by you

im no longer deathly afraid of needles/hospitals/surgeries/etc, they only make me mildly uncomfortable

but yeah i wanted to talk abt this shit i overcame despite myself bc i want you to know you can overcome it too

if you wouldve asked me of 3 years ago to go through that shit, i wouldnt have been able to and i wouldve let it get worse out of fear alone

i had to push myself beyond anything ive ever been through and i came out of it a stronger, braver person

i wanted to talk abt this bc its officially been a year free from that cancer, and while my experience definitely wasnt as harrowing as others go through every day, im proud of myself and how i got through it
i had to walk with a cane for a while but by the time september rolled around i was back in school in a fuckin dance class bustin moves (with minor difficulty lmao)
since then my recovery has been perfect, i stopped needing pain meds after the tube was taken out and with regular scans to make sure it isnt reforming anywhere im feeling fucking great

i ended up walking out, missing a good chunk of muscle in my right leg and a drainage tube hangin out of me lmao

so i went home and slept a fuck ton and ate noodles

anyways, i go back, they do a pregnancy test, i love in asexual, and we continue

i woke up and me n the nurse started chattin, he said i wont remember the conversation ever happening and i said "bet" and i still remember what he looks like
like i had a horrible panic attack getting an iv in for the first time when i got my first ct scan, i was about to have a huge chunk of my leg muscle removed but i was vibing as FUCK fr

SO

i dont talk abt this often but i do believe in god, im baptised and believe jesus died for me etc etc

with this feeling of peace, the only way i can describe it is being calmed by god themself, like genuinely

everything in me SHOULD have been screaming in fear but i wasnt

so then the day arrives, february 23rd 2021

i have to go to the surgery center alone bc of 🅱️ovid, and where i thought id be having a panic attack. i am 100% calm

i felt no fear at all whatsoever

(ofc i was actually terrified but being able to share and laugh with the ppl i love helped a lot)

then i go thru my regular ct scans n shit as time passes, keeping an eye on it yknow

so after being told i have cancer, naturally, i went to work anyways

cut to me joking around and making memes to cope

this meme is actually how i told both my cousin and one of my best friends so s/o to them for being real ones abt it https://t.co/poZUzbKIGr

thankfully, he told me that i wouldn't need chemo or anything and that its a very easy fix, surgery to pop that fushigi ball lookin ass outta there

yknow, surgery, that thing im terrified of

this all ended up happening around end december

cut to beginning of february 2021,
i was about to leave for work when my surgeon called with the results of my biopsy.
he told us it was a Myxofibrosarcoma, a type of slow growing, painless, cancerous tumor
got out of there w minimal emotional damage (as someone who was very afraid of hospitals/needles/being cut open/etc) and went home
(i actually talked to them the entire time abt the process bc i could only occasionally feel pressure on my leg, idk why i was so genuinely curious abt the process while high but anYWAYS)

anywaYYYS i was scared shitless day of biopsy, everyone was super nice and reassuring! ive also never had anaesthesia so i was like 0.0, they gave me a twilight sedation and it certainly mellowed me out lmao but i didnt fall asleep or anything

surgeons great! he's so kind and just an overall great guy (which is great bc i usually get really bad anxiety w male doctors)

now ive never had any sort of surgery done ever, the most thats ever happened to me is one time i got blood drawn for testing

i almost passed out
they said it looks like itd begun to harden, but was still the same size so we got in touch with an orthopedic surgeon and planned a needle biopsy

like two days pass and it got tighter and started actually hurting a bit when i tried stretching, so i told my mom and we went back to the specialist. i got a second ultrasound done (dont by one of my cousins who worked there s/o lmao)
